subSubSection.paragraph:
Male terminalia.
(
Fig. 4B
) Black; epandrium with long macrosetae ventrally and narrowed posteriorly, with a short projection markedly pointed downwards (
Fig. 4D
); hypandrium narrow, with long setae laterally, medioapical region with concavity; subepandrial sclerite with two lobes laterally covered by tuft of small setae, apex rounded; sternite 8 with mid-posterior projection sub-trapezoidal, expanded posteriorly (
Fig. 4E
); gonocoxite curved upwards, with apex pointed, almost sickle-shaped, apical fourth surrounded by minute spines (
Figs. 4G,H
); gonostylus curved, with apex pointed, external region with a median keel and inner region with spines (
Figs. 4G,H
); phallus with two prongs, ejaculatory apodeme wide in lateral view (
Fig. 4F
).
